<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en"
      lang="en" metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
      i18n:domain="launchpad">

<body>

<metal:leftportlets fill-slot="portlets_one">
  <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-rosetta" />
  <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-foaf" />
</metal:leftportlets>

<metal:rightportlets fill-slot="portlets_two">
  <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-malone" />
</metal:rightportlets>

<div metal:fill-slot="main">

  <h1 i18n:translate="">Welcome to The Launchpad!</h1>

  <p i18n:translate="">The Launchpad is a collection of services for
    projects in the open source universe. You can register your
    project, and collaborate with the open source community on translations,
    bug squashing and the code you write.
  </p>

  <form action="/products/" method="get">
    <table>
      <tr>
        <td>
          <input name="text" size="30" />
          <input type="submit" value="Search" />
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table>
    <p class="formHelp">
      Use this form to find an open source application. Enter any part of
      the application name, title or description, and click "Search".
    </p>

  </form>

  <h2>Most Active Projects</h2>

  <p>The following projects are making the most active use of Launchpad
  services (translation and bug tracking):</p>

  <img src="/++resource++product_icon.gif" />
  <b>The Ubuntu Distribution</b>
  [<a href="/distros/ubuntu">View</a>]<br />
  Ubuntu uses the Launchpad for all translation and bug tracking.

  <hr />

  <img src="/++resource++product_icon.gif" />
  <b>GnomeBaker - CD Burning Application</b>
  [<a href="/products/gnomebaker">View</a>]<br />
  GnomeBaker is a popular CD burning GUI application for the Gnome desktop
  environment. It uses the Launchpad primarily for translation services
  through Rosetta.

  <hr />

  <img src="/++resource++product_icon.gif" />
  <b>Bazaar - Distributed Revision Control</b>
  [<a href="/products/bazaar">View</a>]<br />
  Bazaar is a distributed revision control system that is based on Arch. It
  uses the Launchpad for bug tracking.

  <hr />

</div>

</body>
</html>
